t the balance between result accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK/documentation/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK/SBSDKGS1Handling":{"abstract":[{"text":"GS1 message handling options.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The GS1 standard defines a key-value format for business-centric data that can be encoded into many 1D and 2D barcode types.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"https:\/\/ref.gs1.org\/standards\/genspecs\/","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/SBSDKGS1Handling","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotbarcodescannersdk\/sbsdkgs1handling","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGS1Handling"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGS1Handling"}],"title":"SBSDKGS1Handling","type":"topic"}},"variantOverrides":[{"patch":[{"path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK~1documentatio